Area sports briefs (Oct. 21) 
From staff reports Order Reprint of this Story High school cross country 
The Myrtle Beach boys and girls cross country teams took home victories in the Region VIII-AAA meet held at Wilson on Wednesday. 
On the boys’ side, Senior Ethan Epstein (17:35) finished first, while Seahawks eighth grader Tyler Flannelly (18:26) took second. Other Myrtle Beach finishers: Francisco Garcia (5th, 18:55), Austin Parker (8th, 19:27), Tanner Dunn (11th, 19:34), Curt Caudle (12th, 19:39), Cameron Friend (23rd, 21:10). 
Epstein, Flannelly, Garcia and Parker were all named to the All-Region team. 
On the girls’ side, Myrtle Beach’s Morgan Apperson (20:50) was first, Kailey Flannelly (21:39) was third and Rachael Woodard (22:26) was fourth. All three were named to the All-Region squad. High school girls tennis 
Green Sea Floyds 5, Hannah-Pamplico 2 | The Trojans’ season came to an end. Green Sea Floyds took a victory on Tuesday but they fell just short of a playoff spot out of Region VIII-A, finishing third behind Johnsonville and East Clarendon. 
Singles – Kaylee Jordan (GSF) d. Lauren Hyman 6-1, 6-1; Courtnee Faulk (GSF) d. Jordan Fennell 6-2, 6-0; Ellie Stone (HP) d. Sefa Kienast 6-2, 7-5; Hali Hutchinson (GSF) d. Leah Provau 6-1, 6-0; Emmy Kienast (GSF) d. Elana Watkins 7-6 (7-5), 7-5. 
Doubles – Jordan/Faulk (GSF) d. Hyman/Fennell 6-4, 6-2; Jenna Hyman/Mary Grace Mims (HP) d. Chance Caulder/Tiffany Watt 6-3, 6-4. 
Records – Green Sea Floyds 8-5, Hannah-Pamplico 0-12. High school volleyball
